<seg id=1> News Minister Lamer: "Blaze Never Dies" Demonstrators Should Not Become Tools of External Forces </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur) Malaysia News Minister Mohamed Lamer said that demonstrators taking part in "Blaze Never Dies" should not become the tools of external forces. On the contrary, they should find wiser ways to express their minds. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said, compared with resorting to violence and creating turmoil, it is more effective to express thoughts in a rational manner. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Malysia News Agency reported that Mohamed Lamer told the media after attending Family Day activities held by the News Ministry yesterday, that the government has taken measures to let people express their thoughts sufficiently. The 500 "mind speaking centers" set up all around the country let people express their opinions and comments to the country using an approriate approach. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said that government will study the comments and opinions expressed by the people, and improve accordingly, to meet the demand of the public. </seg>
<seg id=6> He emphasized that this is the way a democratic nation conducts itself. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He advised people taking part in demonstrations to think carefully about the repercussions. The fact that all the people had devoted themselves to the nation's development since Malaysia became independent 41 years ago, lead to today's prosperity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that as demonstrators gained support from foreign forces and revolted against the government, they didn't think they were betraying national unity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> He expressed, "If foreigners invest in Malaysia, they are warmly welcomed, but if they pay demonstrators money, we are sure to protest." </seg>
</p>
